	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64501965"><p><div class="quote"><p>There are 3 main disciplines that study the human mind: Anthropology, Sociology, and Psychology.</p></div><p>All three cover aspects of human behavior but only one studies the brain. Concepts of "mind" probably belong as much to philosophy just like "soul" is theological. I have no idea what either of those are and doubt that humans have them.</p><p>Psychology is a big umbrella, including everything from what people would call "hard science" (evidence-based, empirical knowledge) like cognitive science (not the same-named therapy) to pseudoscientific just-so stories like evolutionary psychology. Calling it all the same la<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64501965">

